class TestT45ScatterGatherCorrectness:
    """T4.5 — scatter/gather/index_put template correctness tests.

    Tests the scatter_atomic Slang template end-to-end via
    ``_dispatch_scatter_atomic`` (direct template dispatch, bypassing
    Inductor stock codegen).  Compare against CPU eager mode as ground truth.

    These tests exercise the template with float32 data and int64 indices,
    which covers the common NLP (embeddings), GNN, and MaxPool2d-backward
    use cases.  Each test uses unique cache keys to avoid SPIR-V cache
    collisions across test cases.

    The template was structurally fixed in the T4.5 pass:
      - int64 indices read via ``asint()`` (bit reinterpretation, not value cast)
      - Atomic add resolved via ``import atomics;`` (canonical implementation)
      - Output placed last in tensor list for correct dirty-buffer tracking
      - All tensors made contiguous before dispatch
    """

